<div class="ref-intro">
  <h1>REST API Reference</h1>
  <p>The standalone server exposes a complete REST API at <code>/api</code>. All responses follow <code>{ "ok": true, "data": ... }</code> or <code>{ "ok": false, "error": "message" }</code>. CORS is enabled for all origins. An interactive Swagger/OpenAPI UI is available at <code>http://localhost:3000/api/docs</code> when the server is running.</p>
  <ul class="capability-list">
    <li>Full CRUD for boards, cards, columns, comments, logs, and attachments</li>
    <li>Fuzzy and metadata-scoped search: <code>?q=release&amp;fuzzy=true&amp;meta.team=backend</code></li>
    <li>Card forms submission and webhook management</li>
    <li>Storage migration endpoints</li>
    <li>Board-scoped variants for every card operation</li>
  </ul>
  <div class="usage-example">
    <strong>Create a card via API</strong>
    <pre><code>curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/tasks \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"content": "# My task", "status": "todo", "priority": "high"}'</code></pre>
  </div>
</div>

